# Cursor Hackathon Seoul 3rd

- GitHub: https://github.com/stack1245/Cursor-Hackathon-Seoul-3rd
- Theme: vibe coding with Cursor; build a working AI/public-data product in one day
- Bonus track: use Seoul Open Data Plaza (서울 열린데이터광장) for urban problems (traffic, environment, welfare, safety)
- Prefer fast iteration: small vertical slices, demo-ready UI, clear README for judges
- Default stack unless specified: Next.js or Vite + React, TypeScript when possible
- Keep secrets out of git; use `.env.example` for required env vars
- Write in Korean for user-facing copy unless the product targets English users

## Git branch workflow (3-person team)

- `main`: demo/stable only. Merge from `dev` before final presentation.
- `dev`: integration branch. All feature work lands here first.
- Feature branches (one person each):
  - `feat/ui` — frontend, pages, styling, demo UX
  - `feat/api` — backend routes, server actions, auth
  - `feat/data` — Seoul open data fetch, parsing, AI logic

### Daily flow

1. `git pull origin dev` before starting work
2. Work on your `feat/*` branch only
3. Commit often with small messages
4. Merge your branch into `dev` when a slice works (avoid long-lived divergence)
5. Do not commit directly to `main`

### Conflict tips

- Split by folder when possible: `app/`, `components/`, `lib/`, `api/`
- Whoever touches shared files (`package.json`, root config) coordinates in chat first
